		"Name": "Daikyu",
		"Details": "Named for an anicent Japanese longbow and first produced in 3055, the Daikyu is armed for long-range combat. The design has a high ground speed for its weight, allowing it to dictate the range it engages the enemy at and keeps it in optimal range for its guns. The Daikyu DAI-01 is the stock model, built on a 350-rated XL engine with Endo-Steel bones, and is equipped with an ER PPC, LRM-5, and twin Ultra AC/5s. For close-range combat it has a solitary Medium Laser. 12 tons of armor is acceptable protection for its sniping combat role and three total tons of ammo for the guns is generally enough for shorter engagements.",
